18. Any other disease, metabolic dysfunction, physical examination finding, or clinical laboratory finding that contraindicates the use of an investigational drug, may affect the interpretation of the results, or may render the patient at high risk from treatment complications;
19. Treatment with a live, attenuated vaccine within 4 weeks prior to initiation of study treatment, or anticipation of need for such a vaccine during atezolizumab treatment or within 5 months after the final dose of atezolizumab;
20. Current treatment with anti-viral therapy for HBV;
21. Treatment with investigational therapy within 28 days prior to initiation of study treat-ment;
22. Prior treatment with CD137 agonists or immune checkpoint blockade therapies;
